result.execSummary:
The defendant Zeb C Ebel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Resisting an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol.  Not to possess or consume any controlled substances without a valid prescription and then only take in the amount and frequency prescribed. No contact with the victim(s) unless they consent and probation agent consents.

Complete any counseling, evaluations, programs and assessments, including AODA assessment, as appropriate resulting from the Department's COMPAS assessment. Cooperate with any and all conditons of mental health commitment or proceedings.

Defendant Zeb C Ebel in court, in custody.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews events in file, reviews memo from DOC Agent Cassandra Downing. Deputy Schwartz indicates defendant has now provided a DNA sample.  Agent Downing indicates defendant continues to refuse to sign any releases.  Court questions whether refusal to sign those releases could result in revocation of his probation. Agent Downing not sure if defendant will be revoked or not, she'd have to discuss that issue with her supervisor. Defendant feels he has the right to refuse to sign those releases. Atty Pelrine makes statement. Defendant responds. Court makes statement to defendant, indicates to defendant he needs to sign those releases or face revocation of his probation. Defendant signs release form.
DC Jail Request for Sentence Modification - Defendant requests good time credit. Court denies request, responds - probation - condition time - no good time. DTE

Defendant Zeb C Ebel in court with attorney Eric R. Eickhoff.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Minute sheet. State gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters no contest plea to Cts. 1 & 3. Court dismisses Ct. 2 but reads in for sentencing. State/Defense make joint sentencing recommendation. Court makes statement, imposes sentence. Bond is no longer in effect.

Defendant needs some time to get new counsel in place. Court removes 3/22/16 jury trial from the calendar. Court advises defendant he's to appear in court in person for all future court proceedings. Defendant is not allowed to call in for any more hearings. Bond remains in effect.  Status conference scheduled for April 18, 2016 at 10:00 am.
